	* src/shapelib/Makefile.in (1.2): CVS cleanup.

2006-11-10 21:48  tvrusso

	* configure.ac (1.153), src/Makefile.am (1.41),
	  src/shapelib/LICENSE.LGPL (1.1), src/shapelib/Makefile.am (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/Makefile.in (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/Makefile_shapelib_orig (1.1), src/shapelib/README
	  (1.1), src/shapelib/README.tree (1.1), src/shapelib/dbf_api.html
	  (1.1), src/shapelib/dbfadd.c (1.1), src/shapelib/dbfcreate.c
	  (1.1), src/shapelib/dbfdump.c (1.1), src/shapelib/dbfopen.c
	  (1.1), src/shapelib/libtool (1.1), src/shapelib/makefile.vc
	  (1.1), src/shapelib/makeshape.sh (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/mkinstalldirs (1.1), src/shapelib/shapefil.h (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/shapelib.def (1.1), src/shapelib/shapelib.html
	  (1.1), src/shapelib/shp_api.html (1.1), src/shapelib/shpadd.c
	  (1.1), src/shapelib/shpcreate.c (1.1), src/shapelib/shpdump.c
	  (1.1), src/shapelib/shpopen.c (1.1), src/shapelib/shprewind
	  (1.1), src/shapelib/shprewind.c (1.1), src/shapelib/shptest.c
	  (1.1), src/shapelib/shptree.c (1.1), src/shapelib/shptreedump.c
	  (1.1), src/shapelib/shputils.c (1.1), src/shapelib/stream1.out
	  (1.1), src/shapelib/stream1.sh (1.1), src/shapelib/stream2.out
	  (1.1), src/shapelib/stream2.sh (1.1), src/shapelib/stream3.out
	  (1.1), src/shapelib/contrib/Makefile (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/ShapeFileII.pas (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/dbfcat.c (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/dbfinfo.c (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/makefile.vc (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/my_nan.h (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/shpcat.c (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/shpcentrd.c (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/shpdata.c (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/shpdxf.c (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/shpfix.c (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/shpgeo.c (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/shpgeo.h (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/shpinfo.c (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/shpproj.c (1.1),
	  src/shapelib/contrib/shpwkb.c (1.1): Add shapelib as an internal
	  library, and use it if we don't find an external one.

	  Make a loud warning if we do so, because the result of this is that
	  we'll have a bigger executable.

	  This commit is bigger than it needs to be, because it includes all
	  of shapelib, including the contrib directory.

	  Added an automake-generated Makefile for this thing.

	  Builds only a static library, and calls it "libshape.a" instead of
	  "libshp.a" so that if we use ask to use the static one while there
	  is also an external one installed, the linker doesn't pull in the
	  shared library one unbidden.

	  This stuff can be tested on a system with libshp installed by
	  configuring with "--without-shapelib"

	  I will be removing Makefile.in because it's not supposed to be in
	  CVS.  My mistake.

2006-11-09 16:23  we7u

	* src/xa_config.c (1.162): Changing the default window size on
	  initial startup.  The minimum width/height are set up in
	  main.c:create_appshell() anyway, so we can't reduce the window small
	  enough to cause segfaults by doing this change.

2006-11-09 16:21  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.723): Changed one comment.  No code changes.

2006-11-06 01:16  tvrusso

	* README.win32 (1.135): Add information about problems with Cygwin
	  ImageMagick.  The notes in the README.win32 refer to "recent
	  versions" of cygwin containing ImageMagick 5.5.7, which is very
	  outdated.  Current versions of Cygwin come with 6.0.4, and there are
	  real problems due to that version being linked with Display
	  Postscript support --- X.org stopped supporting that, and now
	  ImageMagick doesn't work on Cygwin unless you find a few DLLs off
	  the net.

	  The paragraph I added here points the user at an article that
	  explains the issue and shows two workarounds (installing the DLLs or
	  building ImageMagick from source code instead).

2006-11-03 20:31  we7u

	* src/util.c (1.217): Adding a diff by Tapio Sokura, which a few
	  comment changes by me.  Thanks! This fixes the lower-case callsigns
	  problem for internet paths.

