	  when measuring distances/areas on the map.  Needs to be generalised
	  and linked to all the places display of an area might be desired.

2006-09-19 13:55  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.589): Removing the '*' after our callsign when
	  injecting packets into the internet (our injection ID that we add).

2006-09-15 16:59  tvrusso

	* src/interface.c (1.261): Inexplicable fix for an equally
	  inexplicable but very persistent problem.

	  My Kenwood D700 complains loudly ("EH?") almost every time Xastir
	  tries to set MYCALL before a posit.

	  This commit adds a carriage return right before MYCALL is sent.  For
	  whatever reason, this eliminates the problem.  Clearly, the d700
	  gets in some strange state where the first command sent after
	  re-entering command mode is not recognized every time.

	  Since a failure of MYCALL to be set before transmit can mean the
	  wrong callsign (or NOCALL) being attached to a posit, this is
	  potentially a significant fix.  I will comment more on it in a
	  follow-up email to the users mailing list.

2006-09-15 16:53  we7u

	* INSTALL (1.88): A tweak by Chip, N1MIE.

2006-09-11 01:03  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.588): Backing out the igate changes until they can be
	  tested further.  They appear to have broken most or all igating ->
	  RF.

2006-09-09 00:35  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.587), src/main.c (1.720), src/main.h (1.95),
	  src/messages.c (1.69), src/messages_gui.c (1.71), src/popup_gui.c
	  (1.27), src/track_gui.c (1.60): Implementing command-line flags
	  for tracking a station and for disabling popups plus disabling Send
	  Message dialogs on incoming messages.  May need some more tweaking
	  to get rid of all popups, but this should be a good start.

2006-09-08 18:10  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.586): Attempting to igate more types of packets to
	  RF, for the cases where it is appropriate to do so.  This should fix
	  the directed query problem, at least when gating _to_ RF.  Will look
	  at the other case as well (gating->INET), which may not be broken.

2006-09-02 23:43  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.585): Adding parsing for RDF packets, with checking
	  to make sure they really _are_ RDF packets this time.

2006-09-01 13:21  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.584): Added a date/timestamp to bearing/distance
	  popup for emergency packets.

2006-09-01 13:05  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.583): Tweaking the processing of emergency packets
	  (Mic_E packets and standard packets) so that the packet gets
	  processed twice if the first time comes up with a 0.0 distance
	  (which means an unknown distance).  This often allows us to match
	  our distance check ( < 280 miles ) the first time a packet is
	  received, instead of having to wait for the 2nd occurrence of the
	  packet.  Also:  We now bring up a popup with the bearing and
	  distance to the emergency station if it passes our checks.

2006-09-01 11:46  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.582): Added another comment in the RDF section.

2006-09-01 11:45  we7u

	* src/messages_gui.c (1.70): Changing input focus to the first
	  message box after sending each message.  For D700 or D7 mode to make
	  typing messages easier.

2006-08-31 21:36  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.581), src/main.c (1.719), src/maps.c (1.499),
	  src/maps.h (1.64), src/util.c (1.216), src/util.h (1.48): Writing
	  wx alerts to file in the correct format now.  Storing/restoring wx
	  alerts from file.  Fixed a bug in the weather alerts code where they
	  wouldn't draw right away.

2006-08-31 21:27  we7u

	* src/wx_gui.c (1.47): Skipping NULL alert entries instead of
	  returning when we hit the first one.  This lets us see all of the
	  active alerts.

2006-08-30 19:29  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.580), src/main.c (1.718), src/main.h (1.94),
	  src/messages_gui.c (1.69), src/xa_config.c (1.160): Logging for
	  messages and weather alerts.  Starting to add more buttons to the
	  Send Message->Change Path dialog.

2006-08-30 19:21  we7u

	* src/Makefile.am (1.40): Putting the files in correct alphabetical
	  order.

2006-08-30 11:38  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.579): This change implements the capability to
	  receive messages that were sent to our other SSID's.  We don't ack
	  them.  They cause a Send Message box to pop up like normal except
	  there's a special note prepended to each message line stating which
	  SSID the message was sent to.  This allows us to catch messages sent
	  to our other stations and respond to them if desired.  We skip
	  displaying these messages if the message originated from our
	  station, as two message boxes for the same QSO is very confusing
	  (and unnecessary).

2006-08-30 11:12  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.260): Fixes for KISS mode when using "DIRECT
	  PATH".

2006-08-29 22:34  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.578), src/main.c (1.717): Adding context-sensitive
	  Send Message To option to the mouse menu.

2006-08-29 22:26  we7u

	* src/messages_gui.c (1.68): Changing to APRHH and APHH as the
	  TOCALLS which mean a HamHUD.

2006-08-29 22:24  we7u

	* src/view_message_gui.c (1.35): Making "Mine Only" take precedence
	  over the range in the View->Messages dialog.

2006-08-29 14:31  we7u

	* src/messages_gui.c (1.67): Minor fixes to the Send Message
	  changes.  Tied the select_station_type capability into the
	  New/Refresh Callsign button as well.

