	  data_lock block to make sure it doesn't get corrupted by another
	  thread.

2006-08-19 22:19  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.257): More correct fixes for truncation
	  problem with new incoming data queue code.

2006-08-19 18:54  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.256): A fix for the circular queue pointer
	  problem.  The read pointer was not getting advanced in the same
	  manner around the queue as the write pointer, giving us an
	  off-by-one error.

2006-08-19 17:42  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.255): A temporary fix to the new queue code
	  problem where it truncates the last character off the strings.

2006-08-18 21:52  tvrusso

	* src/map_shp.c (1.125): Remove commented-out ifndef of
	  label-skipping code.  It won't be needed.

2006-08-18 15:28  we7u

	* src/map_shp.c (1.124): Adding an #ifndef block for Tom Russo to
	  play with.  Currently commented out.  If the block is enabled it
	  will cause Xastir to draw every label for each polyline instead of
	  skipping some based on zoom level.

2006-08-18 13:57  we7u

	* src/map_shp.c (1.123): Added some comments.

2006-08-18 11:07  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.254), src/interface.h (1.37), src/main.c
	  (1.711): Shortening the delay at the end of UpdateTime() again to
	  10.  Global variables for passing data from the read threads to main
	  have been changed to a circular queue.  This lets us queue up data
	  from the read threads when we're busy drawing maps and such, then
	  process it quickly when we're freed up.

2006-08-18 11:02  we7u

	* src/x_spider.c (1.52): Shortening delays so that we don't corrupt
	  packets if we're fed them quickly by the pipe from Xastir.

2006-08-17 12:59  we7u

	* src/database.h (1.36): Renaming a function parameter so that it's
	  not confused with a global variable name.

2006-08-17 12:47  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.572): Renaming a function parameter so that it won't
	  be confused with a global variable name.

