	* src/objects.c (1.38): Updating the Edit and Delete CAD Objects
	  dialogs at more places:
	  *) When we create the first vertice on a new polygon
	  *) When we hit either the Done or Cancel buttons on the Close
	     Polygon dialog.

2006-08-01 14:49  we7u

	* src/objects.c (1.37), src/util.c (1.211): Effectively removing
	  the rounding code that was added on 6/21/2006.  The rounding was not
	  done properly to take into account overflow from seconds to minutes,
	  or from minutes to degrees.

2006-08-01 12:49  we7u

	* src/popup_gui.c (1.25): Bumping up the min size for popup
	  messages slightly.

2006-08-01 12:40  we7u

	* src/popup_gui.c (1.24): A start at fixing the problem where a
	  popup message will come up too small on the screen and can't be
	  resized.  We now set a minimum size and don't fix the size, so it
	  can be resized if necessary to read the message.

2006-07-31 13:42  we7u

	* src/objects.c (1.36): Fixed double-dash option for CAD objects.
	  Update Edit/Erase CAD object dialogs if objects are changed.  Use
	  "<Empty Label>" names if no actual label is selected.  Commented out
	  one message to STDERR during normal pre-defined objects processing,
	  fixed up another message here to use get_user_base_dir() or
	  get_data_base_dir() as appropriate.

2006-07-31 13:30  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.253): Notifying the operator if emergency
	  beacon mode is enabled but no transmits are actually occuring, for
	  various reasons.

2006-07-31 13:28  we7u

	* src/messages.h (1.19): Cranking up max message windows from 10 to
	  25.

2006-07-31 13:27  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.708): Warning the user if ALTNET is enabled on
	  startup (can be confusing when a new user sets this and then sees no
	  stations).  Setting a fixed beacon interval of 60 seconds if
	  emergency beacon mode is enabled.

2006-07-31 13:25  we7u

	* config/language-Dutch.sys (1.212), config/language-English.sys
	  (1.201), config/language-French.sys (1.202),
	  config/language-German.sys (1.209), config/language-Italian.sys
	  (1.202), config/language-Portuguese.sys (1.199),
	  config/language-Spanish.sys (1.209): Adding more strings for
	  popup messages throughout the code, plus language strings for CAD
	  Objects.

2006-07-25 14:53  we7u

	* src/util.c (1.210): A first attempt at snagging course/speed out
	  of the previous posit if the last posit doesn't have it, for
	  dead-reckoning purposes.  It will only do this if the previous posit
	  is still within the dead-reckoning timeout period.  The goal here is
	  to do dead-reckoning properly for stations which alternate
	  GPGGA/GPRMC sentences (GPGGA don't have course/speed).

2006-07-24 19:04  we7u

	* src/draw_symbols.c (1.95): Removing dead or useless code.
	  Reorganizing some of the tests where we determine whether to draw a
	  particular symbol or attribute based on whether it is in the current
	  view.

2006-07-24 19:01  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.554): Changing to setting flags in the station record
	  when it's our station or object/item, then checking flags, instead
	  of checking the "call_sign" or "origin" constantly throughout the
	  code with string compares.  Got rid of the second drawing iteration
	  where we were drawing new stations to the screen _and_ to
	  pixmap_final.  We now draw to the screen and rely on the next full
	  screen-update to do the rest.

2006-07-24 18:54  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.707): Fixing the -geometry flag so that it works
	  for strings like: "-geometry -0-0"

2006-07-22 14:47  tvrusso

	* src/dbfawk.c (1.32): Possible fix for bug that prevents dbfawk
	  files with a single field in the dbffields list from working unless
	  a colon is added to the end of the list.

	  This appears to be a very platform dependent bug, as I have never
	  been able to reproduce the problem.  But the fix is still valid ---
	  the issue is that no null terminator is added to a field name unless
	  a colon is found.

	  This fix doesn't break anything, but I'm unable to verify that it
	  actually fixes the problem reported, since I have never actually
	  seen that problem in action.

2006-07-20 20:05  we7u

	* src/maps.c (1.485): Dump a couple of messages out from
	  map_indexer() to STDERR.  This makes it evident why Xastir is so
	  busy when first started up in a fresh config directory, if there are
	  a lot of maps present on the system.

2006-07-20 19:28  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.706): Nope, 50 was too slow, but 25 looks good so
	  far.

2006-07-20 19:23  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.705): Slowing down the main UpdateTime() loop
	  again.  We seem to keep up with a 2.6 kernel with nexttime=50.
	  Previously 10.

2006-07-19 14:40  we7u

	* src/igate.c (1.56), src/interface.c (1.252), src/main.c (1.704),
	  src/maps.c (1.484), src/messages.c (1.65), src/xa_config.c
	  (1.157): Fixes to get rid of complete path in the config file for
	  variables that need to change between different configs.  If a user
	  has specified a complete path (other than the default path), Xastir
	  will honor it.  If the default path is there, Xastir will shorten it
	  so that multiple configs may use it.

2006-07-19 11:27  we7u

	* src/database.h (1.34), src/db.c (1.553), src/list_gui.c (1.43),
	  src/objects.c (1.35): Getting rid of many of the is_my_call()
	  invocations, instead setting flag bits in the DataRow->flag variable
	  to specify whether it's our callsign-SSID or whether it's an
	  object/item owned by us.  This gets rid of literally millions of
	  string compares.

2006-07-18 00:41  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.552): Skip doing dead-reckoning if scale > 8000.
	  Doing point-caching of last-point-drawn in draw_trail() to reduce
	  the amount of drawing we do when it's the same screen pixel over and
	  over (when zoomed out).

2006-07-18 00:38  we7u

	* src/database.h (1.33): Adding a new flag definition in
	  preparation for a rewrite of the is_my_call() function.

2006-07-17 16:12  we7u

	* src/map_WMS.c (1.22), src/map_geo.c (1.68), src/map_tiger.c
	  (1.50): Patch for bug 1522493 by Dan Brown, n8ysz:  The caching
	  "bad" files problem.  It should whack things out of the cache if,
	  for whatever reason, they're unusable.

2006-07-17 11:57  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.703), src/xa_config.c (1.156), src/xa_config.h
	  (1.8): More tweaks by Dan Brown, n8ysz:  Cleaned up the
	  get_user_base_dir() in xa_config.c to be more careful about
	  returning complete paths.

2006-07-16 19:02  tvrusso

	* src/color.c (1.18), src/map_geo.c (1.67): Clean up transparency
	  code for .geo maps, removing debug output.

	  This now works properly for 16 and 24 bit DirectColor/TrueColor
	  displays.  It is horribly broken for 8-bit displays, but as far as I
	  can tell it was horribly broken *before* I started.  On 8-bit
	  displays the WMSRadar image doesn't even get displayed, transparent
	  or not, before *and* after my changes.  I was unable to figure out
	  why.

2006-07-16 17:21  tvrusso

	* src/color.c (1.17), src/map_geo.c (1.66): An interim commit of
	  partial fixes to the transparency problem on .geo files.

	  Mostly committing this to get it to a machine that has a display
	  that isn't 24-bit for testing.

	  Lots of cruft in here needs editing out after testing is complete.

2006-07-14 18:50  we7u

	* README.Getting-Started (1.28), xastir.1 (1.12): Updates by Dan
	  Brown, n8ysz.

2006-07-14 15:53  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.702), src/xa_config.c (1.155): Additions/fixes to
	  implement alternate Xastir config directories.  Patch submitted by
	  Dan Brown, n8ysz.

2006-07-13 12:10  we7u

	* scripts/get-NWSdata (1.7): Fixing up the domain names so that
	  they all match (for consistency).

2006-07-12 17:47  we7u

	* scripts/get-NWSdata (1.6): Updating one NWS shapefile name to
	  latest version.

2006-07-12 17:47  we7u

	* README.MAPS (1.84): Updating the text for NWS Shapefile names to
	  match the NOAA website.

2006-07-12 14:24  we7u

	* src/draw_symbols.c (1.94): A fix for the bug where text-on-black
	  obscure text above/below slightly due to the black background.  We
	  now separate the text by another pixel and the problem goes away.

2006-07-11 16:06  tvrusso

	* WMSRadar.geo (1.8): Tweak transparency value.  For some time now,
	  the actual "no reflection" value that's been coming in has been hex
	  value  0x010101, not "0x000000".  On 24-bit displays that means that
	  the default file was displaying with an opaque nearly-black
	  background instead of a transparent one.

	  The actual no-reflection value returned by the WMS server has
	  changed back and forth between 0x000000 and 0x010101 often in the
	  history of the WMSRadar file and will probably need to be changed
	  again some time in the future.  It has been pretty consistently
	  0x010101 for several weeks now.

2006-07-11 14:38  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.551): Fixing incorrect timestamps for local station.
	  This was causing track points to get expired immediately so that the
	  station didn't show a track if being run with only a GPS interface.

2006-07-11 13:02  we7u

	* src/draw_symbols.c (1.93): Fixes for dead-reckoning 180 degree
	  problem and for the DR arc being slightly off.

2006-07-11 12:18  we7u

	* src/draw_symbols.c (1.92): Removing dead code.

2006-07-11 12:06  we7u

	* src/draw_symbols.c (1.91): More efficient dead-reckoning code
	  plus commenting out unused sections of code.

2006-07-11 11:41  we7u

	* src/draw_symbols.c (1.90): More tweaks to dead-reckoning.  We now
	  attempt to display the arc and the DR'ed trail if either the symbol
	  or the DR'ed symbol are on-screen.  Added an "if" clause to the
	  DR'ed symbol drawing so it is only drawn when on-screen.  Commented
	  out old code that we're not using anymore.

2006-07-11 11:01  we7u

	* src/util.c (1.209): Another fix by Dan Brown, n8ysz.  This one
	  keeps the log files at or below the max logfile size.

2006-07-11 10:59  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.251): Removing a duplicate include line.
	  Thanks to Dan Brown for finding it.

2006-07-11 03:15  we7u

	* src/draw_symbols.c (1.89): Implenting DR arcs again.  Problems
	  near/at 180 degrees, but other than that it seems to work fine.

2006-07-10 17:24  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.550): Disabling the XtRemoveGrab() function call
	  which causes warnings on some OS'es.  I don't believe we actually
	  need it.  We'll find out for sure when more users try out this
	  version.

2006-07-10 17:23  we7u

	* src/draw_symbols.c (1.88): Test code for re-enabling the
	  dead-reckoning arc's.  Not complete/correct yet, but it's a start.

2006-07-10 16:40  we7u

	* src/wx.c (1.63): Fixes by Mike Loebl, kb1mts, to add barometric
	  pressure and humidity decoding to ARNE format.

2006-07-10 12:57  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.701): Fixing high CPU usage problems on FreeBSD,
	  changing nexttime from 2ms to 10ms.  Thanks to Carl Makin for this
	  tweak.

2006-07-10 11:09  we7u

	* src/util.c (1.208): Fixes by Dan Brown, n8ysz, for Xastir bug
	  1518805:  "Log files can fill up hard drive".  We now limit a log
	  file to about 2MB at which point we roll it over to a new filename
	  and create a new empty file to write to.  We keep up to 3 of these
	  backup files plus the current log file at any given time, which
	  makes for between 6MB and 8MB of data that we keep.

2006-07-07 16:10  we7u

	* README.Contributing (1.13): Added a section by Dan Brown.

2006-07-07 15:06  we7u

	* scripts/BUILDRPMS (1.8): Tweaking the rev number.

2006-07-06 16:23  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.700): Fixes by Dan Brown, n8ysz, for Xastir bugs
	  1515197 "segfault if XASTIR_USER_BASE no existing" and 1517761, "No
	  error check on config dir mkdir".

2006-07-06 15:36  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.699), src/track_gui.c (1.56): Fixes for the blank
	  label problem on sliders with certain releases of OpenMotif.  This
	  relates to problems with using XtVaTypedArg within an
	  XtVaCreateManagedWidget() function.  Instead we now call
	  XmStringCreateLocalized() before the call, and XmStringFree()
	  afterwards.

2006-07-05 14:17  we7u

	* src/Makefile.am (1.38), src/main.c (1.698): A patch to add
	  compile time/date to the Help->About dialog, by Dan Brown, N8YSZ.

2006-06-29 17:04  we7u

	* src/xa_config.c (1.154): Making the igate -> RF path default be
	  "WIDE2-1".

2006-06-27 14:25  we7u

	* src/igate.c (1.55): Reorganizing the logic slightly to make it
	  easier to understand w.r.t. the gating of objects/items/stations to
	  RF via the nws-stations.txt file.  Added/updated several comments.

2006-06-23 16:03  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.549): Adding more comments.  No code changes.

2006-06-23 15:31  we7u

	* src/igate.c (1.54): Changing igating->RF around so that if a
	  station or object name is found in the nws-stations.txt file, it
	  will get gated to RF whether or not "TCPXX" is found in the path.
	  This allows more types of things to be gated to RF if manually
	  specified in the nws-stations.txt file.

2006-06-22 12:42  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.548): Mostly changes to comments, but changed the
	  error ellipses from black to white.  Still need to draw truncation
	  rectangles instead in some cases.

2006-06-21 14:49  we7u

	* src/objects.c (1.34): Tweaking the rounding in objects.c

2006-06-21 13:12  we7u

	* src/util.c (1.207): Changing some comments.

2006-06-21 12:41  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.250), src/util.c (1.206): Fixing up posits so
	  that we round properly instead of truncating the higher resolution
	  digits.  For some-odd reason the fprintf doesn't round up properly
	  at 0.5, so we add a 0.01 to the number so that it rounds up.

2006-06-21 11:51  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.547): Changing one comment.

2006-06-20 12:55  we7u

	* src/database.h (1.32), src/db.c (1.546), src/draw_symbols.c
	  (1.87): An attempt to do the error ellipses for position packets.
	  This is most likely not the display we'll finalize on, but it's a
	  start.  We draw circles for the less-precise posits, but as Tom
	  Russo pointed out they should probably be rectangles.  Also, the
	  GPGGA/GPRMC/GPGLL code needs some work w.r.t. these.

2006-06-19 21:47  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.545), src/draw_symbols.c (1.86), src/draw_symbols.h
	  (1.23): Making sure we don't try to do dead-reckoning on stations
	  that have position ambiguity enabled.

