2006-03-14 01:40  we7u

	* config/language-Dutch.sys (1.210), config/language-English.sys
	  (1.199), config/language-French.sys (1.200),
	  config/language-German.sys (1.206), config/language-Italian.sys
	  (1.200), config/language-Portuguese.sys (1.197),
	  config/language-Spanish.sys (1.207), src/objects.c (1.31):
	  Shortening "Area" to "A" for CAD objects.  Also shortening the unit
	  descriptions.

2006-03-14 01:32  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.530): Refusing to do the emergency popups
	  until/unless we have a position for a station.  It's hard to help
	  someone if we don't know where they are at.  This keeps Xastir from
	  annoying the crap out of people every 30 minutes if a posit for that
	  station isn't coming in, but a packet with certain keywords _is_
	  coming in regularly.

2006-03-10 20:56  we7u

	* INSTALL (1.85): Added another note about libtiff-3.8.0

2006-03-10 20:45  we7u

	* INSTALL (1.84): Adding solution text regarding the
	  libgdal/libgeotiff GTIFProj4ToLatLong problem.

2006-03-10 20:28  tvrusso

	* README.MAPS (1.77): Fix a handful of mispleellings and mistales.

2006-03-10 20:09  tvrusso

	* README.MAPS (1.76): Rearrange some of the discussion of how to
	  manipulate randomly mutilated GeoTIFF files.

2006-03-10 16:16  we7u

	* README.MAPS (1.75): Adding a section about using gdal_translate
	  to convert crappy geoTIFF's to usable ones.  Thanks to Tom Russo for
	  the info on how to do this.

2006-03-10 16:15  we7u

	* INSTALL (1.83): Slightly changing some wording in the gdal
	  section.  Nothing of importance.

2006-03-09 20:47  we7u

	* INSTALL (1.82): Updating various library revision numbers.  Added
	  a note about a possible geoTIFF conflict when installing GDAL.

2006-03-09 20:46  we7u

	* src/map_tif.c (1.39): Making sure that Proj.4 error messages
	  appear only under the correct circumstances.

2006-03-09 02:43  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.529): Initial implementation of a distance check for
	  warnings/alerts.  Default is set to 280 miles or kilometers
	  (whichever mode you are set in), and the check defaults to ON,
	  meaning it will check each time whether the station is within that
	  distance.  This version has no user controls for the new
	  functionality implemented yet.

2006-03-08 02:44  we7u

	* src/wx.c (1.55): Fixing the rounding for some of the values that
	  can be negative, coming from weather stations.

