	  This makes main.c quite a bit smaller.

2005-09-24 18:21  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.616): Proper numeric checks for Global.top
	  size/offsets, for deciding whether to make the 2nd Xastir window
	  (the first visible window) copy either set of parameters.

2005-09-24 18:00  we7u

	* src/list_gui.c (1.37), src/main.c (1.615): Changing variables
	  used in XtVaGetValues() calls to "Dimension" or "Position".  Adding
	  an out-of-range check for dimension for the case where we're
	  attempting to discover whether the first window has had -geometry
	  specified.

2005-09-24 00:18  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.614): First working version of the "-geometry"
	  command-line flag.  Will hopefully know soon if it works on all
	  platforms we support.  Let the testing begin!

2005-09-23 19:01  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.613): "-geometry" switch now works for sizing the
	  application (instead of "-g"), but the X/Y offsets still don't work.

2005-09-23 02:18  tvrusso

	* src/main.c (1.612): Give "appshell_width" and "appshell_height"
	  initial values of 0.  This allows the contents of the xastir.cnf
	  file's SCREEN_WIDTH and SCREEN_HEIGHT to be used if no geometry is
	  specified in -g.  As it was, if one didn't give -g then these two
	  settings in the config file were ignored and a 100x100 window
	  appeared on every start-up.

2005-09-22 20:32  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.611): A fix for Xastir hanging if the -g flag is
	  used but only offsets are specified.

2005-09-22 20:07  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.610): Initial implementation of the "-g" geometry
	  command-line flag.  It supports sizing the application, but doesn't
	  support X/Y offsets yet.  That's in the works though.

2005-09-22 05:29  we7u

	* config/language-Dutch.sys (1.187), config/language-English.sys
	  (1.177), config/language-French.sys (1.177),
	  config/language-German.sys (1.182), config/language-Italian.sys
