	* src/awk.c (1.26): Tweak by John Laxson, KC0PZN, to speed up
	  dbfawk on MacOSX.  Thanks!

2005-05-05 19:19  we7u

	* README (1.23): Getting rid of version number where it's not
	  needed.  Will save us some work in the future.

2005-04-29 22:06  kd6zwr

	* src/interface.c (1.220): Fixes for segmentation faults on
	  Solaris.  Sending a NULL pointer to a %s argument to any of the
	  *printf() functions (actually strlen() inside it) causes the fault.
	  This patch intializes two vars to "" instead of NULL, {Which is
	  OK!!} protects a function by whacking NULLs into ""s, and moves a
	  debug printf below a NULL check.

2005-04-26 18:24  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.219): If an interface goes down due to a
	  connection being lost or inactivity, the 1st check_ports() call will
	  bring it back up now.  Previously it would wait for the 2nd
	  check_ports() call before bringing it back up.

2005-04-25 19:44  we7u

	* README.MAPS (1.58): Added a paragraph about splitting large
	  Shapefiles into tiles.

2005-04-25 19:44  we7u

	* README.Getting-Started (1.17): Minor changes to a couple of
	  sentences.

