	* src/map_tiger.c (1.24), src/map_cache.c (1.7), src/map_cache.h
	  (1.3): More map caching mods by Dan Brown, n8ysz.

2004-11-30 05:14  we7u

	* src/messages.c (1.40): Getting rid of extra message transmit
	  before timeout.  This causes us to transmit exactly MAX_TRIES times,
	  instead of MAX_TRIES + 1.

2004-11-29 20:55  we7u

	* src/database.h (1.2), src/db.c (1.399), src/messages.c (1.39):
	  Adding a "CANCELLED" indicator to the Send Message box for those
	  messages that made it to transmit from the queue but got manually
	  cancelled by the user.

2004-11-29 19:58  we7u

	* src/messages.h (1.9), src/messages.c (1.38): More RF-friendly
	  decaying algorithm for messages.  We start at 7 seconds and double
	  the interval each time.  Timeout occurs at about 2 hours if no ACK
	  received.

2004-11-29 19:37  we7u

	* src/x_spider.c (1.30): Changing from LF to CRLF in lines sent to
	  clients which have connected to the server port.

2004-11-28 18:03  tvrusso

	* acinclude.m4 (1.27): Change probe for db.h to use AC_TRY_COMPILE
	  instead of AC_CHECK_HEADER, so that we can apply the same usability
	  test that is present in map_cache.c.

2004-11-28 02:56  we7u

	* src/x_spider.c (1.29): Making sure that lines sent out the server
	  port have "\r\n" at the end.  Before we just had '\r', which doesn't
	  correspond to the way the internet servers did it.

