	* src/util.c (1.126): Changing one variable so that it local to
	  where it is used instead of at the top of the routine.  Changed
	  flags to be counting flags instead of booleans, so we can later use
	  them to count digipeater types.  Added some comments.

2004-11-01 20:34  we7u

	* src/util.c (1.125): Tweaking the path-check code so that
	  trace,wide2-2 and wide,wide2-2 paths and similar are allowed.

2004-11-01 17:11  tvrusso

	* configure.ac (1.101), src/util.c (1.124): Add probe for strndup
	  to configure.ac.  Ifdef use of strndup in src/util.c.

	  strndup is a GNU extension and not portable to non-GNU systems.

	  strdup is portable, so is used if strndup isn't available.

