2004-09-17 19:22  we7u

	* INSTALL (1.50), README.Getting-Started (1.8), acinclude.m4
	  (1.17), configure.ac (1.99), src/popup_gui.c (1.16): Implementing
	  the "--without-errorpopups" configure flag.  If invoked,
	  popup_messages() writes to STDERR instead of causing a popup dialog
	  to appear.

2004-09-17 17:12  tvrusso

	* src/main.c (1.520): Put Cygwin-specific setting of nexttime into
	  the UpdateTime function.

	  Remove the two Cygwin-specific usleep(2) from the end of UpdateTime.

	  With these changes, running xastir on Cygwin under Win2K on a 2GHz
	  machine went from taking up 90+% of the CPU to taking around 20% ---
	  most of that in system processes, and mostly that high when X events
	  are being processed.

2004-09-16 19:31  we7u

	* configure.ac (1.98): Bumping the revision to 1.4.1, as we just
	  did a stable release at 1.4.0.

2004-09-16 14:47  we7u

	* src/xa_config.c (1.125): Changing default sound command from
	  "vplay" to "play" as it is much more common.

2004-09-16 14:00  tvrusso

	* src/map_gnis.c (1.11): Quick, trivial commit both to make sure
	  I'm set up right and to remove a slightly annoying error message
	  when I'm looking at New Mexico with GNIS: Add "ruin" as a recognized
	  gnis entry type.

	  Ideally, this mapping of gnis entries to zoom level limits should be
	  in metadata rather than a large if/elseif/elseif... block, but
	  that's another issue.

2004-09-15 20:19  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.385): Re-ordering "if" statements to speed things up
	  slightly.

2004-09-15 19:59  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.384): Another speedup (lower CPU usage).

2004-09-15 19:44  we7u

	* src/alert.c (1.83): Reducing CPU usage of normal_title().

2004-09-15 19:43  we7u

	* src/db.h (1.58): Slowing down minimum object timing by another
	  five seconds.  Reduces how often we look through our database,
	  keeping CPU usage down.

2004-09-15 17:08  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.383): Swapping two "if" statements in a loop, as the
	  is_my_call() function appears to be faster than the boolean
	  operations to determine whether it's an object/item.

2004-09-14 19:32  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.382): Making is_my_call() and
	  check_and_transmit_objects_items() more efficient.  Found during
	  profiling that these routines were eating up CPU.

2004-09-14 02:50  we7u

	* INSTALL (1.49), configure.ac (1.97): Adding the
	  "--with-profiling" flag.  Updating docs to reflect it.

2004-09-13 19:56  we7u

	* src/map_shp.c (1.73): Changing label storage to a hash table
	  instead of an array, to speed things up.  Using the first character
	  of the string as the hash index.  Tried using lower 7 bits of first
	  two chars, and lower 6 bits of first two chars: Profiling showed
	  that using the first character was faster.

2004-09-13 19:54  we7u

	* src/rotated.c (1.13): Moving math into appropriate parts of loop
	  to speed it up.  Anything that is static through all iterations of a
	  loop is moved outside that loop for speed.

2004-09-10 23:09  we7u

	* src/draw_symbols.c (1.56): Implementing a cache for the most
	  recent five symbols used.  Speeds up drawing by quite a bit (found
	  by profiling).

2004-09-10 19:26  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.519): More speedups found by profiling.  Checking
	  for new gps map only once per second now, updating the stations
	  count on the status line once per second instead of continuously.

2004-09-10 16:19  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.518): Adding some Cygwin-specific usleep's in
	  UpdateTime() in order to reduce CPU usage on those systems.

2004-09-10 15:49  we7u

	* src/awk.c (1.23): Sped up awk_find_sym() a bit.

