2004-09-02 17:45  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.516): Fixing the locale for numbers to "C".  We
	  require this in order to be able to write and parse our config files
	  and .geo files properly when the LC_NUMERIC or LANG environment
	  variables are set to something else.  This affects the printf and
	  scanf sorts of functions.

