	  courtesy of Tom Russo.  Thanks!

2004-08-27 20:09  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.514): Fix for high CPU-usage when time skips
	  backwards.  This fix causes Xastir to sleep a bit in the
	  UpdateTime() loop until time catches up again, thereby avoiding the
	  problem.  It also dumps a message out to STDERR as it goes into/out
	  of this mode.

