2004-08-10 19:51  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.504), src/x_spider.c (1.16), src/x_spider.h (1.5):
	  Code that changes the process name in "ps" listings for the x_spider
	  daemon and client connections.  Doesn't work on other operating
	  systems, and doesn't work for "top" listings.

2004-08-09 18:32  we7u

	* src/x_spider.c (1.15): Disabling the Nagle algorithm and enabling
	  SO_KEEPALIVE for the server port connections.

2004-08-07 18:12  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.190): Modified AGWPE parsing routine and
	  associated code.  We've now turned off "monitor" mode and turned on
	  "raw" mode in AGWPE.  The "raw" packets get thrown into our standard
	  KISS decoding routines, which gives us the possibility of supporting
	  OpenTrac (a binary protocol) and digipeating on AGWPE ports in the
	  future.  The "monitor" mode decoding has been left for now, but
	  later on we'll probably delete it.  Also:  Added output to STDERR
	  for the AGWPE server version and for the port descriptions.

2004-08-06 19:57  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.363): Change to comment.  No code changes.

2004-08-06 16:29  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.189): Minor changes to comments and debug
	  output messages.

2004-08-05 20:02  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.362), src/festival.c (1.11), src/main.c (1.503),
	  src/interface.c (1.188), src/sound.c (1.8), src/util.c (1.114),
	  src/util.h (1.26): Re-wrote the agwpe parsing code.  It should be
	  more bulletproof now, but still has some debug stuff in it for NWS_
	  and NWS- messages.  Fixed a segfault caused by one of the new
	  strncpy() functions that I switched to in util.c:spell_it_out().

2004-08-04 20:04  we7u

	* config/language-Dutch.sys (1.142), config/language-English.sys
	  (1.136), config/language-French.sys (1.137),
	  config/language-German.sys (1.141), config/language-Italian.sys
	  (1.139), config/language-Portuguese.sys (1.136),
	  config/language-Spanish.sys (1.146), src/main.c (1.502): Changing
	  the Modify Object/Item dialogs so that you must adopt an object/item
	  that you don't own before you're allowed to delete it.  Adopting or
	  Modifying someone else's object causes you to transmit it as a live
	  object owned by you.  After that, you may delete it.  If the client
	  that previously owned it saw your live object, it'll know that you
	  own it and that you can delete it.  Without this adoption process,
	  UI-View32 clients will hold on to an object that you're trying to
	  kill.

2004-08-04 19:07  we7u

	* help/help-English.dat (1.81): Tweaking the note about AGWPE
	  network authentication.  We can use that now.

2004-08-04 18:54  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.187), src/interface_gui.c (1.74): Fixes for
	  AGWPE.  Network loging with authentication should work now.

2004-08-03 21:21  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.361): Fix to allow objects/items to get through the
	  server port and get igated.

2004-08-03 20:04  we7u

	* src/util.c (1.113): Small tweak to valid_inet_name() where it is
	  checking for the "aprsd" string.  It didn't appear to be general
	  enough to catch all possibilities.  Now it should be.

