	  (1.6), src/wx_gui.c (1.32): Adding the capability to finger the
	  WXSVR if an object/item and has "WXSVR" in the path.  This is from a
	  new button "Fetch NWS Alert" in the Station Info dialog.  It takes
	  the place of the FCC/RAC button if the above conditions are met.

2004-05-13 17:17  we7u

	* configure.ac (1.85): Moving the ImageMagick check so that it is
	  the absolute last check, so that it doesn't mess up the GDAL check
	  either.  Added comments stating that the IM check should stay as the
	  last check.

2004-05-13 16:51  we7u

	* configure.ac (1.84): Moving the ImageMagick test to later in the
	  configuration.  It appears to mess up the tests for other libraries
	  if it fails.  Now only the GDAL test is below it.

2004-05-12 20:49  we7u

	* src/alert.c (1.68): Additional comments.

2004-05-12 19:33  we7u

	* scripts/overlay.pl (1.3): Correcting the math for lat/long.

2004-05-12 18:56  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.161): Making sure that the AGWPE path is
	  upper-case.

2004-05-12 18:45  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.160): Fixing a bug in AGWPE path for
	  objects/items.  This bug was caused by a different use of variables
	  between the output_aprs_data() and output_my_aprs_data() functions,
	  and then copying code from one to the other without changing the
	  variables.  Variable names are now more common between them, so this
	  problem should be less likely to occur in the future.

2004-05-12 16:44  we7u

	* scripts/overlay.pl (1.2): Changes to comments.

2004-05-12 16:16  we7u

	* scripts/overlay.pl (1.1), scripts/Makefile.am (1.12): Adding
	  overlay.pl, which creates either Xastir log file format or Xastir
	  object.log format files from CSV files.  Used to create object
	  overlays (actually APRS Items in this case) out of spreadsheet data.

2004-05-11 17:07  we7u

	* README.win32 (1.95): Added a comment about an error caused by
	  line-wrap in the Shapelib Makefile.

2004-05-10 20:51  we7u

	* src/main.h (1.60), src/main.c (1.454): Adding #ifdef's for
	  "OLD_PTHREADS", which knock out the SIGUSR1 handler if
	  "OLD_PTHREADS" is defined in "main.h".

2004-05-10 19:33  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.315): Proper code for randomizing the object/item
	  transmit times a bit.

2004-05-10 16:39  we7u

	* scripts/Makefile.am (1.11): Adding a few of the newer scripts to
	  the install portion.

2004-05-09 02:54  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.453), src/db.c (1.314): Tweaking the object/item
	  timing to make sure that any changes to an object cause the object
	  to immediately go to the initial state of the decay algorithm.

2004-05-09 01:55  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.313): Fixing the random number modulus operations for
	  transmitting objects/items.  It appears however that the rand() and
	  random() functions are broken on this system, always returning 0.

2004-05-07 21:09  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.312): Reducing the randomizing of object/item TX
	  times from 33% of interval to 20% of interval.

2004-05-07 20:45  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.311): Randomizing object/item transmit a bit so that
	  they don't get transmitted together when restarting with active
	  objects/items.  This causes them to diverse fairly well after about
	  the third transmit iteration.

2004-05-07 20:21  we7u

	* src/util.c (1.101): Adding some comments.

2004-05-07 18:02  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.310): Fix for objects/items:  If we're using the name
	  of one that has already been killed, we now delete the old record
	  completely before creating the new one.  This keeps us from drawing
	  tracklines from one to the other or keeping info that doesn't apply
	  to the new object/item.

2004-05-07 16:19  we7u

	* src/util.c (1.100): Fixing the logging of objects/items.  There
	  were problems with removing spaces from Items which made them not
	  found in the search, and problems with comments in front of lines in
	  the log file.

2004-05-07 16:16  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.309), src/db.h (1.48): Comment changes.  No code
	  changes.

2004-05-06 23:27  we7u

	* src/messages.c (1.28): Reducing the initial time interval between
	  transmitted messages from 15 to 7 seconds.

2004-05-06 23:19  we7u

	* src/db.h (1.47), src/messages.c (1.27): Minor comment changes.

2004-05-06 21:40  we7u

	* src/db.h (1.46), src/db.c (1.308), src/main.c (1.452):
	  Implementing the decaying algorithm for timing of object/item
	  transmits, similar to how Bob Bruninga does it in aprsDOS.  Also
	  added a segfault fix for moving Items (same fix as done earlier for
	  moving Objects).

