	* src/util.c (1.98): Backing out the changes done earlier today.
	  Will try again to implement higher resolution NMEA strings at a
	  later date.

2004-04-01 04:16  shadow

	* README.MAPS (1.32): Add pointer to Census 2003 data. Add pointer
	  to geocoder data files.

2004-03-31 18:56  we7u

	* src/util.c (1.97): Extending the NMEA sentence decoding to handle
	  DD MM.MMMM format, which the new Tinytrak-3 chips can put out.  That
	  resolution ends up being 0.6 counts of our Xastir coordinate system,
	  so we need to resolve down to that level to avoid losing much.

2004-03-30 22:58  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.307): Changing from circles to an 'X' for marking a
	  found address.

2004-03-30 20:49  we7u

	* src/xa_config.c (1.115): Saving/restoring the Mark Destination
	  button state for the Find Address function.

2004-03-30 20:44  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.306), src/geo.h (1.3), src/geocoder_gui.c (1.4):
	  Added a togglebutton that enables/disables the marking of the
	  destination for the Find Address function.

2004-03-30 20:21  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.305), src/geo.h (1.2), src/geocoder_gui.c (1.3):
	  Initial attempt at marking the destination target for a Find Address
	  query.  There's not capability yet for removing the marking, but you
	  can always seek another address and it will move to the new one.
	  Will probably change to some other marking at some point (a big 'X'
	  perhaps?), and need to find a way to remove the mark that makes
	  sense.

2004-03-30 16:58  we7u

	* src/geocoder_gui.c (1.2): Minor re-arranging of the Find Address
	  dialog's widgets.

2004-03-29 23:57  we7u

	* src/io-mmap.c (1.2): Adding an include to get rid of compiler
	  warnings about memcpy().

2004-03-29 23:40  we7u

	* src/LICENSE.geocoder (1.1), src/geo-client.c (1.1),
	  src/geo-find.c (1.1), src/geo.h (1.1), src/geocoder_gui.c (1.1),
	  src/io-common.c (1.1), src/io-mmap.c (1.1), src/io.h (1.1),
	  src/Makefile.am (1.15), src/main.c (1.448), src/main.h (1.59),
	  src/xa_config.c (1.114): Geocoding support added by Derrick J
	  Brashear, based off code written by Daniel Egenor that was released
	  under GPL license.

2004-03-26 18:17  we7u

	* Makefile.am (1.24): Moving the .geo files into a subdirectory
	  called "Online".

2004-03-25 16:35  we7u

	* src/gps.c (1.39): Enabling setuid priviledge at the point where
	  settimeofday() is called.  Thanks to William Baguhn, kc9asi, for
	  pointing this out.

