	  Bruce Bennett, KB8ROP.

2004-03-23 18:01  we7u

	* src/wx.c (1.37): Changes by Bruce Bennett.

2004-03-22 22:12  we7u

	* src/map_geo.c (1.30): Moving an #ifdef so that no compiler
	  warnings are generated when ImageMagick support is missing.

2004-03-22 21:52  we7u

	* acinclude.m4 (1.13): Fixes for Cygwin regarding comm ports.

2004-03-22 17:23  we7u

	* README.win32 (1.82): Adding instructions to side-step the
	  "detecting devices" hang on WinXP.

2004-03-21 20:58  rzg

	* help/help-English.dat (1.77): Added info on the comment field in
	  interfaces; started a new tally of what changed since release.

2004-03-19 22:38  we7u

	* src/map_gnis.c (1.7): Removing trailing spaces while reading
	  lines in from GNIS files.  They are notorious for having many spaces
	  at the ends of the lines.

2004-03-19 20:37  we7u

	* src/map_shp.c (1.47): The rest of the code needed for the
	  XReadBitmapFile() call failure, in order to make sure everything
	  keeps running.

2004-03-19 20:34  we7u

	* src/map_shp.c (1.46): Getting rid of the exit(1) that we were
	  doing when the XReadBitmapFile() call was failing during long
	  runtimes.  It's annoying if the bitmap is not found but it shouldn't
	  kill all of Xastir in that case.  I'll be checking to see if further
	  changes to the code are necessary though to prevent segfaults
	  happening later in that part of the code.

2004-03-19 17:52  we7u

	* scripts/split_gnis.pl (1.2): Added an RCS tag.  Still needs a
	  copyright blurb.

2004-03-19 17:51  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.158): Fixing the long transmit delay, which
	  was in port_write at the final select() call.

2004-03-19 03:21  jtwilley

	* scripts/split_gnis.pl (1.1):

	  Added split_gnis.pl to scripts directory.

	  The split_gnis.pl script will take any number of state-wide GNIS
	  files listed on the command line and create smaller files based on
	  county names.

2004-03-18 23:14  we7u

	* src/maps.c (1.403): Adding S57 map format to Xastir's supported
	  map types.  File extension currently has to be ".s57" for these
	  types of maps to be recognized by Xastir.

2004-03-18 18:11  we7u

	* scripts/ozi2geo.pl (1.2): Changed one comment.

2004-03-18 17:58  we7u

	* scripts/ozi2geo.pl (1.1): Initial attempt at a conversion script
	  from OziExplorer .map format to Xastir's .geo format.  This version
	  works with the one example map I had to work with.  More than likely
	  more work will be needed on the script as more types of maps are
	  tried.

2004-03-15 23:49  we7u

	* scripts/split_gnis.bash (1.2): Added a comment about "dos2unix".

2004-03-15 23:47  we7u

	* scripts/split_gnis.bash (1.1): Script written by William Baguhn,
	  kc9asi.  Splits a GNIS files into smaller pieces which are more
	  quickly loaded by Xastir when zoomed in.

