	  checkin.

2004-03-01 17:31  we7u

	* README.MAPS (1.30): Changing notes regarding where to find free
	  DRG maps.

2004-03-01 02:40  we7u

	* config/language-Dutch.sys (1.122), config/language-English.sys
	  (1.118), config/language-French.sys (1.118),
	  config/language-German.sys (1.122), config/language-Italian.sys
	  (1.120), config/language-Portuguese.sys (1.118),
	  config/language-Spanish.sys (1.128), src/interface_gui.c (1.64):
	  Tweaking the Interface Start/Stop dialog so that it is much more
	  readable.

2004-02-29 20:31  we7u

	* config/language-Dutch.sys (1.121), config/language-English.sys
	  (1.117), config/language-French.sys (1.117),
	  config/language-German.sys (1.121), config/language-Italian.sys
	  (1.119), config/language-Portuguese.sys (1.117),
	  config/language-Spanish.sys (1.127), src/db.c (1.302), src/main.c
	  (1.446), src/main.h (1.58), src/xa_config.c (1.112): Added two
	  new trail sliders to the timing dialog.  They both control whether
	  trails are displayed, one based on max distance, one based on max
	  time.  If either max distance or max time are exceeded for new
	  trails, that segment is not drawn.  Does not affect trail points
	  that have already been received, just new trail points.

2004-02-28 03:12  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.445): Modifying the Move function so that it drops
	  through all the dialogs and doesn't require any OK buttons to be
	  pressed to effect the move.  This is useful for drawing the expected
	  route of a SAR team and documenting it via Shapefiles.  It's much
	  faster to do so now.  Downside: Unintentionally moving an object
	  gets an automatic confirm, and you'll have to move it back manually
	  or else edit the object.log file by hand and read it in again.

2004-02-28 02:00  we7u

	* config/language-Dutch.sys (1.120), config/language-English.sys
	  (1.116), config/language-French.sys (1.116),
	  config/language-German.sys (1.120), config/language-Italian.sys
	  (1.118), config/language-Portuguese.sys (1.116),
	  config/language-Spanish.sys (1.126), src/main.c (1.444),
	  src/xa_config.c (1.111): Adding a "Disable Posit Dupe-Checks"
	  option to Configure->Defaults.  Disables the 30-minute dupe-checks
	  that Xastir does when each packet is received.  Does not affect
	  igate dupe-checks.

2004-02-28 01:26  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.301), src/main.h (1.57), src/util.c (1.96): Turning
	  off trail-point dupe-checking when reading in objects/items from
	  file.  This lets us show SAR teams leaving and returning to base
	  later, without having the last trail segment missing.

2004-02-28 01:00  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.300): Updating some comments.

2004-02-27 23:42  we7u

	* help/help-English.dat (1.75): Adding notes about trails and why
	  some segments don't display.

2004-02-27 22:58  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.299): Changing the distance at which Xastir will skip
	  a track segment, from >1 degree lat/long to >2 degrees.  Any track
	  segment less than 2 degrees in N/S and E/W length will get drawn, as
	  long as the time between posits is less than 45 minutes.  If over 45
	  minutes, the segment gets skipped as well.

2004-02-26 23:25  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.156): New code to avoid opening the same
	  serial port twice for two different interfaces.

2004-02-26 23:19  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.298): Changing some debug code.

2004-02-26 21:48  we7u

	* INSTALL (1.32): Added a note about how to test the festival
	  server by telnet'ing to it.

2004-02-26 20:30  we7u

	* src/map_geo.c (1.24), src/map_tiger.c (1.14), src/track_gui.c
	  (1.29): Fixing the problem where a failed internet download (map
	  or tracklog) would cause an older version of the same to get
	  displayed.  We now delete the old filename from our ~/.xastir/tmp
	  directory before attempting the download each time.

2004-02-26 20:07  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.297), src/db.h (1.45): Adding a retry timeout for
	  killed object/items.  We'll now transmit killed objects 11 times
	  before ceasing to transmit them.

