	* src/main.c (1.437): Adding more sprintf's in cases of failure to
	  create symlinks.

2004-01-14 20:07  we7u

	* configure.ac (1.74): Extending one comment.  No code changes.

2004-01-14 20:00  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.436): Minor tweak to two fprintf strings.

2004-01-12 19:44  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.435): Changing back to a previous configuration for
	  the end of the create_appshell() function.  Attempting to get rid of
	    this problem: "attempt to add non-widget child "DropSiteManager" to
	    parent "xastir" which support only widgets" while not re-creating
	    this problem: "Shell widget xastir has zero width and/or height".

2004-01-09 18:57  rzg

	* help/help-English.dat (1.70), src/maps.c (1.397): Map index
	  checking now allows negative layer numbers.  Minor helpfile updates

2004-01-09 16:11  we7u

	* src/map_gdal.c (1.79): More checks for invalid extents while
	  indexing.  If all 0's or outside indexes of the earth, we skip
	  adding it to the index.

2004-01-08 21:38  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.434): Re-establishing the XtRealizeWidget() call in
	  main that was commented out to help fix the "zero width or height"
	  error on startup.  Now we specify a minimum size in the
	  XtVaAppInitialize() call that preceeds it, so the old problem
	  shouldn't reoccur.

2004-01-08 21:34  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.433): Gives an initial size to the application.
	  Makes it appear to come up faster.  Whether or not it actually does
	  is beside the point.  May help to get rid of the initial sizing
	  problem: "Error: Shell widget xastir has zero width and/or height".

2004-01-07 16:42  we7u

	* configure.ac (1.73): Minor tweaks to some AC_MSG_ERROR calls.

2004-01-07 16:42  we7u

	* INSTALL (1.26): Minor tweaks to the make instructions here and
	  there.

2004-01-04 21:37  we7u

	* src/map_gdal.c (1.78): Correcting the limits for OGR indexing.

2003-12-30 15:38  we7u

	* src/maps.c (1.396): Changing startup STDERR output to show which
	  library (Shapelib/OGR) is providing Shapefile support.

2003-12-26 17:26  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.152): Bumping the read/write loop timeouts to
	  100ms.  This should provide reasonable response time when killing
	  ports, yet keep CPU usage low when no data is being read/written.

2003-12-26 16:17  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.151): Bumping the timeout in port_write()
	  select to 500ms.  That timeout is used to jump out of the select()
	  so that we can check whether the interface has gone down.  It does
	  not need to be very small, and in fact causes high CPU usage on
	  freebsd systems if it's below about 1ms.  Linux can handle somewhat
	  smaller delays (100us is ok on Linux).

