	* src/interface_gui.c (1.59): Adding another #include, needed for
	  usleep() call.

2003-08-21 22:01  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.280): Changed some comment formatting.

2003-08-21 21:10  we7u

	* src/interface_gui.c (1.58): Adding a delay after shutting down a
	  port before it is brought up again.  These delays are in the
	  interfaces->properties menu when changing an interface that's
	  running.

2003-08-21 19:31  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.279), src/db.h (1.38): Added a new flag to WeatherRow
	  called wx_storm.  We wet it when we find any kind of a severe storm,
	  then use that flag in our logic that decides how to draw things.
	  This gets rid of wind barbs for some severe storms.

2003-08-21 18:01  we7u

	* scripts/inf2geo.pl (1.4): New revisions by ZL2UMF.  Thanks!

2003-08-21 16:42  we7u

	* src/igate.c (1.25): We now drop generic queries heading to RF.
	  Also tweaked the log reject messages to be more consistent.

2003-08-21 16:30  we7u

	* src/igate.c (1.24): Removed the '*' requirement for TCPXX*, so we
	  now reject anything with TCPXX in it.  Added NOGATE options for
	  dropping packets to all igate functions.  Added generic query
	  rejection for gating to 'net.  Still need to add it into the
	  gate-to-rf code.

2003-08-20 19:55  we7u

	* symbols/symbols.dat (1.18): Changing the "smoke" symbol so that
	  it shows a volcano instead of a smokestack.  This is more inline
	  with the reason the weather server puts out these symbols, and is
	  more recognizable than the smokestack symbol anyway.

2003-08-20 18:05  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.332): Changing the network port check from 7.5
	  minutes down to one minute.  This should reconnect ports more
	  quickly if/when they go down.

2003-08-18 23:16  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.278): Removing a back-slash that got in there
	  accidentally.

2003-08-18 22:46  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.277): Getting the sort order correct for inserting
	  records into the station database.  Didn't work well with the wrong
	  order.

2003-08-18 18:09  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.276): Commenting out some speedup code in
	  station_shortcuts_update_function() that may be causing problems at
	  present.

2003-08-18 17:40  we7u

	* src/maps.c (1.318): Henk's fix to a pointer problem that I
	  created recently.

2003-08-17 06:04  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.275): Fixing a bug in the hash table code which looks
	  for station matches.  Making the clear all stations function faster
	  by clearing out the hash table first.

2003-08-16 01:40  we7u

	* src/maps.c (1.317): Making index_retrieve() faster by relying on
	  alphanumerical ordering of the map files in the index list.  We now
	  save the pointer between runs, and start searching the list at the
	  point we left off.

2003-08-16 01:12  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.331): Minor comment cleanup and removing dead code.

2003-08-16 01:04  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.330): Better pointers for Map Chooser select
	  updates.

2003-08-16 00:53  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.329): Changing from n*n searches to n searches for
	  updating selected bits when closing Map Chooser.

2003-08-16 00:12  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.140): Bumping out of port_read less often.
	  This is only to check whether the thread should be taken down
	  anyway.  If a packet is waiting for us to read it, we'll wake up out
	  of the select() anyway.

2003-08-15 23:55  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.328): Rearranging some if statements to get a
	  little more speed out of it.

2003-08-15 23:11  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.327), src/maps.c (1.316), src/maps.h (1.31): Added
	  caching of XmString values corresponding to the map filenames for
	  the Map Chooser.  The first time bringing up Map Chooser will be at
	  the same speed as before.  Second and succeeding invocations of the
	  Map Chooser should be a bit faster because the XmString's are used
	  from the map index records again instead of being created from
	  scratch each time.

2003-08-15 19:30  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.139): CPU-usage optimization tweak to
	  port_read().

2003-08-15 19:11  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.138), src/main.c (1.326): CPU-usage tweak for
	  dtr_all_set calls.  It was getting called constantly whenever an HSP
	  port was enabled.

2003-08-15 18:51  we7u

	* src/maps.c (1.315): CPU-usage tweak to index_retrieve().

2003-08-15 18:20  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.274): Yet another CPU-usage tweak.  This one is to
	  search_station_name().  It's more efficient now at finding stations
	  in the linked list, using a hash table as a jumping-off point.

2003-08-14 22:02  we7u

	* src/map_shp.c (1.14): Changing the level at which shorelines get
	  drawn.

2003-08-14 21:59  we7u

	* src/map_shp.c (1.13): Setting up more levels at which things
	  won't be drawn.  Will make things faster/less cluttered.

2003-08-14 21:46  we7u

	* src/map_shp.c (1.12): Optimizing shapefile vector drawing.  We
	  don't convert the coordinates for each point now unless we're going
	  to draw the darn thing.

2003-08-14 20:52  we7u

	* src/maps.c (1.314): More speedups.

2003-08-14 20:27  we7u

	* src/map_shp.c (1.11): Added some comments.

2003-08-14 16:12  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.325), src/maps.c (1.313), src/maps.h (1.30),
	  src/xastir.h (1.26): First part of speeding up Shapefile drawing
	  by staying with lat/long values as much as possible, rather than
	  doing conversions to Xastir coordinate system at every step.  The
	  end goal is to do as little math as possible to put pixels on the
	  screen.  These changes give a slight speedup to shapefile drawing,
	  noticeable only when loading lots of maps.

2003-08-13 23:26  we7u

	* src/map_shp.c (1.10): Reverting back to last version.  Floats
	  made CPU-usage worse in this case.

2003-08-13 22:49  we7u

	* src/map_shp.c (1.9): Speedups.  Using floating point operations
	  instead of unsigned longs.

2003-08-13 19:45  gstueve

	* .cvsignore (1.1), callpass/.cvsignore (1.1), config/.cvsignore
	  (1.1), help/.cvsignore (1.1), m4/.cvsignore (1.1),
	  scripts/.cvsignore (1.1), src/.cvsignore (1.1),
	  symbols/.cvsignore (1.1): Ignore generated files within CVS base.

2003-08-13 19:38  we7u

	* src/draw_symbols.c (1.48): Made the symbol() routine more
	  efficient.  Uses much less CPU now.

2003-08-12 18:48  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.137): More performance improvements.

2003-08-12 18:45  we7u

	* src/popup_gui.c (1.13): Another performance improvement.  Only
	  check for expired popups every two minutes.

2003-08-12 17:29  we7u

	* src/bulletin_gui.c (1.21): Another performance improvement.  The
	  timing was set up such that find_zero_position_bulletins() ran every
	  time UpdateTime() was started.  We now wait 15 seconds between each
	  invocation.

2003-08-11 23:57  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.273), src/messages.c (1.24): More optimizations for
	  speed/CPU-usage.  Hash table entry creation is now more efficient.
	  Check_and_transmit_messages now gets skipped if we ran it already
	  that second.

2003-08-11 23:15  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.324): Added a comment.

2003-08-11 23:05  we7u

	* INSTALL (1.15): Added RH9 ImageMagick instructions, courtesy of
	  Wes Johnston.

2003-08-11 22:40  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.272), src/main.c (1.323): Moved station # display
	  code from db.c to main.c:UpdateTime() so that the number of stations
	  will accurately reflect our count even when no packets are coming
	  in.

2003-08-11 22:08  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.136): Another performance/CPU-usage tweak.

2003-08-11 21:48  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.322): Another performance tweak.  This one lets you
	  handle multiple high-speed 'net connections and keeps up with the
	  receive queues.

2003-08-11 21:07  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.135): Performance enhancements.  Helps Xastir
	  to keep up with very fast network interfaces.

2003-08-11 20:24  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.321): Making UpdateTime() run more often, which
	  helps us keep up with fast internet feeds.

2003-08-11 19:57  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.271): Changing how often we check for stations and
	  messages to expire from our database.  This should also reduce CPU
	  usage.

2003-08-11 18:31  we7u

	* src/bulletin_gui.c (1.20): Another CPU-usage tweak.  Running
	  through all of the messages looking for new bulletins every 15
	  seconds instead of every 2.  Keeps mscan_file() calls down a bit,
	  which is using a lot of CPU if run often.

2003-08-11 14:04  n2ygk

	* src/awk.c (1.7), src/awk.h (1.4), src/dbfawk.c (1.2),
	  src/dbfawk.h (1.2), src/testawk.c (1.6): Save a newer snapshot of
	  in-progress code.  Still not baked.

2003-08-09 01:03  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.270): Implementing a 14-bit hash table for station
	  record lookup.  This appears to have a BIG effect on CPU usage.  May
	  be a bit before the codebase is stable again though, but the gains
	  are definitely worth it.  It gives us a feeling for what an SQL
	  database will do for us.

2003-08-08 23:16  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.269): Implemented an array of pointers for the
	  station linked list.  Each entry represents one possible starting
	  letter/number for the callsign.  We use this to speed up the search
	  for a particular record, which is our hardest hitter in terms of
	  CPU-usage right now.  This appears to reduce Xastir's CPU
	  requirements by quite a bit, particularly when a lot of stations are
	  in the database.

2003-08-07 20:47  we7u

	* src/draw_symbols.c (1.47): Backing out one change which broke the
	  port activity symbols.  They're working again now.

2003-08-07 17:01  we7u

	* src/Makefile.am (1.9): Taking out the awk/dbfawk stuff
	  temporarily until it can be compiled on most systems again.

2003-08-07 00:54  we7u

	* src/maps.c (1.312): Another speedup.

2003-08-06 23:19  we7u

	* src/draw_symbols.c (1.46): Speeding up the loading of symbols.

2003-08-06 23:18  we7u

	* src/lang.c (1.9): Breaking out of a loop as soon as we get a
	  non-match.

2003-08-06 17:43  we7u

	* README.win32 (1.63): Added a note regarding Windows not allowing
	  access to files at times.

2003-08-05 14:34  n2ygk

	* src/Makefile.am (1.8), src/awk.c (1.6), src/dbfawk.c (1.1),
	  src/dbfawk.h (1.1), src/testawk.c (1.5): more dbfawk utility
	  functions.  I'll be integrating this into map_shp.c RSN!

2003-08-04 23:13  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.320): Another small change which makes a difference
	  in CPU usage.

2003-08-04 22:36  we7u

	* src/draw_symbols.c (1.45): Changing draw colors only when
	  necessary.  Found this one while profiling using gprof.  May be more
	  to change in this procedure to speed things up a bit..

2003-08-02 17:00  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.319): Tweaked Coordinate Calculator so that it
	  checks lat/long minutes/seconds values for negative numbers and >=
	  60.0.  If out-of-range numbers are found, the error text is
	  displayed in the dialog and a warning message is written to STDERR
	  with a bit more detail on the problem found.  Later this STDERR
	  output should probably go to a popup or the main dialog instead, and
	  language strings should be created for them.

2003-07-31 16:01  we7u

	* src/view_message_gui.c (1.14): Making the Close button larger.

2003-07-31 15:21  we7u

	* src/view_message_gui.c (1.13): Made the View->All Messages dialog
	  resizable in both directions.

2003-07-31 13:00  we7u

	* src/bulletin_gui.c (1.19): Fixed View->Bulletins dialog so that
	  it is resizable in both directions.

2003-07-28 05:20  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.268), src/main.c (1.318): Improved Display Packet
	  Data dialog.  This one is resizable and very fast.  Much better than
	  the previous implementation.

2003-07-27 00:11  we7u

	* symbols/symbols.dat (1.17): Added the MODIS Earth Observation
	  symbol.  Added a comment specifying where to find the color
	  definitions used for symbols.

2003-07-26 16:35  we7u

	* src/map_dos.c (1.9): Commented out some fprintf's that were
	  getting quite verbose when certain Win/DOS maps were loaded.
	  Warnings were that we were trying to call draw/fill polygon routines
	  with 1 or 2 points.

2003-07-25 20:00  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.317): Cranked up the delay on REDRAW from 2 to 3
	  seconds.  Changed the dead-reckoning code to schedule a map redraw
	  instead of doing on itself (which probably duplicated some drawing).
	  CPU usage seems to be down because of these changes.

2003-07-25 18:18  we7u

	* src/gps.c (1.35): Improved GPS parsing code.  Fixed buffer
	  overflow problems and restructured code.

2003-07-25 14:36  we7u

	* src/gps.c (1.34), src/interface.c (1.134): Added
	  line-terminations after strncpy() calls and a bunch of comments at
	  those places as well.

