	* src/db.c (1.265): Making Tropical Storm/Tropical
	  Depression/Hurricane wind speed rings disappear at the ghosting
	  time.

2003-07-16 21:07  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.132): Installing thread cleanup routines.
	  These should take care of unlocking mutex's when the threads
	  terminate for any reason.  Should keep the rest of the program
	  running.

2003-07-16 05:25  we7u

	* README.win32 (1.57): Changing the note about creating the .cvsrc
	  file.  Trying to make it VERY CLEAR that a Unix-type editor must be
	  used.

2003-07-15 22:58  we7u

	* src/util.c (1.79): Changing the begin_critical_section() functio
	  (mutex locks).  If a resource has already been locked, output a
	  warning message and skip trying to lock again.  This should allow
	  Xastir to recover should locks or unlocks be tried twice or more in
	  sequence.  Warning messages will get printed, but the threads should
	  continue to run.

2003-07-15 22:42  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.312): Adding the busy cursor in a couple of places
	  so that we have a better indication of when map drawing is taking
	  place.

2003-07-15 20:46  we7u

	* config/language-Dutch.sys (1.105), config/language-English.sys
	  (1.97), config/language-French.sys (1.101),
	  config/language-German.sys (1.105), config/language-Italian.sys
	  (1.103), config/language-Portuguese.sys (1.102),
	  config/language-Spanish.sys (1.111), src/main.c (1.311): Cranking
	  up the GPS timing if it is set lower than 3 seconds.  We also now
	  present a popup to the user to notify them that the GPS timing has
	  been changed.

2003-07-15 20:23  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.310): Adding a timeout for HSP ports for GPS
	  listener mode.

2003-07-15 19:34  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.131): First attempt at fixing some of the HSP
	  interface's problems.  This one will send strings other than GPGGA
	  and GPRMC through the normal decoding sequence.  That will at least
	  process received TNC strings, which the previous code did not.

