2003-07-03 21:30  we7u

	* src/map_dos.c (1.5), src/map_geo.c (1.3), src/map_gnis.c (1.2),
	  src/map_pdb.c (1.2), src/map_shp.c (1.2), src/map_tif.c (1.2),
	  src/map_tiger.c (1.2): More map interrupting capability.
	  Currently works for resizing quite nicely.

2003-07-03 20:23  we7u

	* src/map_geo.c (1.2), src/maps.c (1.305): Adding in more map
	  drawing interruption capability.

2003-07-03 19:13  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.302), src/main.h (1.46), src/maps.c (1.304): Added
	  some flags that get set by da_resize, which then immediately exits
	  allowing X11 to continue.  If interrupt_drawing_now is set, map
	  drawing ceases after the map we're currently loading is finished.
	  If request_resize is set, then a resize operation is started by
	  UpdateTime.  We can add checks for interrupt_drawing_now to other
	  routines later in order to stop map drawing more quickly.  Next is
	  to do a similar thing for the da_input function, so that a keypress
	  or mouse click can interrupt map loading.

