	  interval.

2003-02-03 05:05  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.204), src/db.h (1.29), src/xa_config.c (1.72): Added
	  a global variable st_direct_timeout which is saved in the config
	  file.  This specifies the timeout value for the ST_DIRECT bit.

2003-02-02 16:42  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.203): Added comments around the ST_DIRECT bit
	  setting/clearing code.  Change the ST_DIRECT bit timeout from 1
	  minute to 1 hour.  This gives stations that transmit only every 30
	  minutes (common) a chance to be seen as an ST_DIRECT station.  As
	  the comments show in that section of code, that timeout value will
	  in the future probably change into a global variable that is set
	  within the config file.

2003-02-02 07:22  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.202): Fixed a pointer-to-integer comparison (compiler
	  warning).  Reformatted the code per Xastir project specs.

2003-02-02 04:42  jtwilley

	* src/db.h (1.28):

	  Added direct_heard variable to station data structure.  This
	  variable is set each time a direct packet is received from a
	  station.

2003-02-02 04:40  jtwilley

	* src/db.c (1.201):



	  Removed old support for direct stations and added new complete
	  direct station support.  Paths with WIDE and TRACE entries of all
	  kinds are properly checked for directness.

2003-02-01 10:14  we7u

	* config/language-Dutch.sys (1.75), config/language-English.sys
	  (1.74), config/language-French.sys (1.75),
	  config/language-German.sys (1.74), config/language-Italian.sys
	  (1.75), config/language-Portuguese.sys (1.72),
	  config/language-Spanish.sys (1.77), src/db.c (1.200), src/db.h
	  (1.27), src/interface.c (1.61), src/main.c (1.210), src/util.c
	  (1.51): Partial fixes for GUI lockups due to lots of
	  locally-controlled objects: Moved delays in interface routine so
	  that they'd only take effect if the interface was up and transmit
	  was enabled (both global and per-interface transmit controls).
	  Added a statusline() the lets us know when we're retransmitting our
	  objects/items.  Delayed transmit of our items for 30 seconds after
	  initial startup.  We will still have delays each POSIT_interval when
	  our objects get sent:  Something like 2 seconds * number of
	  up/tx-enabled interfaces * number of objects.

