2002-11-24 06:11  we7u

	* src/util.c (1.44): Tweaks to the speech stuff so that we don't
	  add commas to the SSID portion of a callsign.  This makes it speak
	  -12 as "dash twelve".

2002-11-24 04:20  we7u

	* README.1ST (1.41): Added a blurb about festival and starting it
	  in server mode.  Useful for those that can't read the English help
	  file (where it is also documented).

2002-11-23 16:18  we7u

	* src/util.c (1.43): Speech stuff now looks for a number in the
	  text (before a dash).  If found, it adds commas so that Festival
	  will speak each letter.  If not found, it feeds the string directly
	  to Festival to let it try to pronounce it.

