2002-11-13 23:31  we7u

	* src/maps.c (1.158): Forcing terraserver map extents in the index
	  to be at the edges of the earth.  Added more statusline messages for
	  loading/indexing maps (more consistent now).

2002-11-13 22:13  we7u

	* src/maps.c (1.157): An attempt to fix the buffer overflow
	  problems with map indexing.

2002-11-13 21:19  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.161): We now delete/recreate our own station record
	  only if we change our callsign.  All other changes just cause an
	  update to the current record.

2002-11-13 20:43  we7u

	* config/language-Dutch.sys (1.53), config/language-English.sys
	  (1.52), config/language-French.sys (1.52),
	  config/language-German.sys (1.52), config/language-Italian.sys
	  (1.53), config/language-Portuguese.sys (1.49),
	  config/language-Spanish.sys (1.54): New "Waiting for GPS data.."
	  string.

2002-11-13 20:40  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.170), src/interface.c (1.53), src/main.c (1.160),
	  src/main.h (1.25): Implemented a countdown from when GPS data
	  goes invalid.  It is decremented each time a posit occurs.  When it
	  reaches zero, posits stop.  Valid GPS data parsing will reset it
	  back to the starting count.  Also reduced the size of the tracked
	  station circles in order to more easily read the station data.

2002-11-13 02:23  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.169): Added another blue circle for tracked stations.
	  Now three concentric circles.

2002-11-13 02:17  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.168): Making a tracked station have both a yellow and
	  red circle to make it easier to see against different map
	  backgrounds.

2002-11-13 02:07  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.167), src/interface.c (1.52), src/main.c (1.159),
	  src/main.h (1.24): Added "my_position_valid" variable, initially
	  set to 1.  As soon as a GPS interface of any type is started up,
	  this variable gets set to zero, and it holds off posits.  Once the
	  first valid GPS position is parsed, this variable is again set to 1,
	  and posits proceed normally.  As Xastir comes up, interfaces are
	  brought up before the first posit, so if a GPS interface is enabled
	  on startup, no posits will occur until the first GPS posit is parsed
	  properly.  This variable could be used later to disable posits when
	  GPS data becomes unusable or stops coming in.  This feature is not
	  implemented yet though.

2002-11-12 23:23  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.166): Changed tracked stations circle from Red to
	  Yellow to make it easier for partially colorblind people to see
	  against a background of topo maps.

2002-11-12 22:56  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.165): Got rid of another bug off the buglist.  Now
	  only stations that are currently visible will be selected for
	  Station Info operations.

2002-11-12 22:15  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.158): Changed the order of startup so that map
	  indexing is completed before interfaces are brought up.

2002-11-12 18:56  we7u

	* src/maps.c (1.156): Changes intended to keep variables from going
	  out-of-bounds.  I'm attempting to get more DRG-Enhanced map formats
	  working.  These changes don't quite make them work, but they do make
	  it better and catch some out-of-bounds problems.

