	* src/igate.c (1.5), src/interface.c (1.19), src/messages.c (1.17):
	  Added/modified some comments.

2002-06-20 19:47  we7u

	* src/interface.c (1.18): Added a 250ms delay after writing each
	  waypoint.

2002-06-20 17:44  we7u

	* src/gps.c (1.14): Added some notes to the waypoint creation
	  routine.

2002-06-20 17:36  we7u

	* src/gps.c (1.13): Fixed problem with lower-case characters when
	  creating waypoints.

2002-06-20 00:17  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.80), src/gps.c (1.12), src/gps.h (1.2),
	  src/interface.c (1.17), src/interface.h (1.5): For those of you
	  with Garmin GPS units:  Set up the audio proximity alarm range for
	  some distance around your station and Xastir will now create
	  waypoints for each APRS station/object/item that it hears within
	  that range.  They'll appear on your Garmin map display as waypoints.
	  Enjoy! You can delete the waypoints by type.  They appear as the
	  circle with the 'X' in the middle.  You may want to change other
	  waypoints to some other type before you play with this new Xastir
	  feature.

2002-06-19 17:53  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.79): Fixed remove_leading_spaces() as it didn't work
	  at all as coded.  It liked to truncate after the first word.  Also
	  fixed some malloc sizes added recently.

2002-06-19 17:44  francais1

	* src/db.c (1.78): strlen, not sizeof

2002-06-19 00:06  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.77), src/db.h (1.9), src/list_gui.c (1.9): Additional
	  memory savings for the node_path variable in the station database.
	  Changed it to a pointer and allocate exact space for the string when
	  stored or updated.

2002-06-18 23:19  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.76), src/db.h (1.8), src/list_gui.c (1.8), src/main.c
	  (1.95): More space savings.  Turned comment into a pointer in the
	  station record and allocate just the space we need for it.

2002-06-18 22:21  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.75), src/db.h (1.7), src/list_gui.c (1.7), src/main.c
	  (1.94): Changed to dynamically-allocated linked list of comment
	  strings in the station database.  This results in memory savings due
	  to no empty strings being stored for stations without comment
	  fields.  It also shows all status and comment strings that have been
	  seen for each station now in the Station Info dialog.  We'll have
	  loads of fun tracking MIC-E expansion on the internet servers now!

2002-06-18 18:55  we7u

	* src/draw_symbols.c (1.8): Simplifying the logic a bit.  Same
	  general idea.

