	  tigermap_intensity in the users config file.

2002-06-07 00:02  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.51): Added a popup dialog for MIC-E emergency
	  messages.  Displays the callsign of the station in trouble.

2002-06-06 22:03  we7u

	* src/messages.c (1.16), src/xa_config.c (1.25): Moved range
	  checking for message_counter to xa_config.  More efficient.  Only
	  needs to be done once when starting up.

2002-06-06 21:45  we7u

	* src/messages.c (1.15), src/xa_config.c (1.24), src/xastir.h
	  (1.9): Converted message_counter to a string.  Changed message
	  sequence numbers to be 2 characters within this range: 0-9A-Za-z.
	  This prevents lockups when messaging with APRS+ stations.

2002-06-06 21:43  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.50): Removed old code.

2002-06-06 18:00  we7u

	* config/language-Dutch.sys (1.20), config/language-English.sys
	  (1.20), config/language-French.sys (1.20),
	  config/language-German.sys (1.20), config/language-Italian.sys
	  (1.21), config/language-Portuguese.sys (1.14),
	  config/language-Spanish.sys (1.22), src/db.c (1.49), src/main.c
	  (1.78), src/xastir.h (1.8): Implemented satellite ack mode, where
	  the Reply/Ack protocol is used to send ack's through satellites, and
	  ack's like "ack001" are disabled entirely.

2002-06-06 17:03  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.48), src/db.h (1.6), src/messages.c (1.14): Changes
	  which implement full Reply/Ack protocol.  This should speed up
	  messaging dramatically when involved in live QSO's with the APRS
	  programs that support this protocol.  This lists currently includes
	  aprsDOS, APRS+, and Xastir.

2002-06-05 20:28  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.47), src/db.h (1.5), src/messages.c (1.13): Marking
	  timed-out messages in Send Message dialog properly.  Small changes
	  to Reply/Ack sequence numbers.

2002-06-04 23:13  we7u

	* src/messages.c (1.12), src/xa_config.c (1.23): Switching to
	  base-90 for message sequence numbers (all the way to lower-case
	  'z').  Also tweaked xa_config.c to help us avoid the message_counter
	  rollover problem.

2002-06-04 22:47  we7u

	* src/messages.c (1.11): Changed from base-91 to base-89 format for
	  message sequence numbers.  This is to avoid use of the '{' character
	  within the sequence.

2002-06-04 22:25  we7u

	* src/messages.c (1.10): Converted outgoing sequence numbers to
	  2-character base-91 encoding.  Added a trailing '}' character to
	  signify that we're Reply-Ack protocol capable.

2002-06-04 21:32  we7u

	* src/messages.c (1.9): Had to take out the '}' from the sequence
	  number as it messed things up.

2002-06-04 21:20  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.46), src/messages.c (1.8): Message sequence numbers
	  are saved through restarts now.  Added more comments.

2002-06-04 20:27  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.45): Changed several comments.  Decoding of Reply/Ack
	  protocol (free-ride ACK's) is now tested and working.  This really
	  speeds up live messaging.  When encoding of the free-ride ACK's is
	  implemented as well it'll speed up messaging even more.

2002-06-04 00:50  rzg

	* README.1ST (1.16), help/help-English.dat (1.12): Updates for
	  tigermap changes and minor bits I missed in the previous update.

2002-06-03 20:30  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.44): Minor changes to Reply/Ack's.

2002-06-03 20:14  we7u

	* src/db.c (1.43): The beginnings of Reply/Ack protocol decode.
	  Not fully tested.  Encode not implemented yet.

2002-06-03 16:45  francais1

	* src/maps.c (1.99): Fixed up imagemagick_options struct a bit.
	  Removed some imagemagick_options stuff from draw_tiger_map because
	  it is not being setup since there is no .geo file.  Fixed
	  draw_tiger_map intensity/levels bug.

2002-06-03 16:21  we7u

	* src/maps.c (1.98): Changing some line widths and colors back to
	  what we had before the weekend.  We're not trying to duplicate the
	  TigerMap servers colors or look-and-feel.  We need more subdued
	  colors so that symbols and tracks show up better on top of the maps.
	  The line widths are necessary in order to more quickly identify
	  major roads without having to rely only on color.

2002-06-03 16:18  francais1

	* src/maps.c (1.97): Removed extraneous ifdef

2002-06-03 15:38  we7u

	* src/gps.c (1.11): Fixes for decoding GPS NMEA sentences where
	  there are 4 digits after the decimal point.  Garmin GPS-35 and the
	  NavMan both put out an extra digit.

2002-06-03 14:59  we7u

	* src/main.c (1.77): Fixed segfault bug in Config_tiger.

2002-06-03 14:23  we7u

	* src/maps.c (1.96): Added another #ifdef around a LevelImage()
	  call.

